<TEXT>
<P>
   TUNICA, MISS. _ What a shame Elvis did not live to see it.
Thirty miles from Graceland a new Las Vegas has sprouted in the
Delta, and lights blaze along the Mississippi River.
</P>
<P>
   Times have certainly changed. In 1990, Tunica County was
officially listed by the Census Bureau as the poorest county in the
United States, a place famous mostly for open-ditch sewers and
clapped-out cars rusting in cotton fields.
</P>
