 ART ADV.: A photo with SCI-MANSON is being transmitted to NYT Photo
Service subscribers.  
 For Immediate Release  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following FEATURE stories for
use by NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   PROFILE-GUSMAO (Jakarta) _ A profile on the man called the
Nelson Mandela of East Timor, the rebel turned politician turned
prisoner who is respected by all sides and seen as the likely
leader of what will be left of a new independent East Timor. By
Indira A.R. Lakshmanan. 1500 words.
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-POLICE (Belfast) _ In the Markets, a largely Catholic
housing project where some 85 percent of the heads of household are
out of work and the police are scorned, there is little enthusiasm
for reforming the police force. By Kevin Cullen. 1180 words.
