<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Washington) _ Among the 23,000 fans watching the
U.S. Open championship between Andre Agassi and Todd Martin Sunday
was Walter Cronkite, wearing a jacket and tie. He was the only one
spotted in the crowd attired so spiffily. Cronkite, bless his
heart, is a generational throwback. Dress codes are vanishing, even
here at the Washington Opera. The new sloppiness, one of the few
things we can't blame on President Clinton, is here to stay. By
MARIANNE MEANS.
</P>
</TEXT>
