   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   REFORM-BUCHANAN (Washington) _ The prospect that Patrick J.
Buchanan would try to become the Reform Party's presidential
nominee could set off an expensive fight rife with fraud and could
bankrupt the organization, the incoming chairman says. 1200 words.
