<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-SPOT-BUDGET-BOS </SLUG>
  
 For Release TUESDAY AMs, September 14, 1999  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Boston Globe plans to move the following stories for use by
NYTimes News Service clients.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR; For questions about stories, contact  &UR; Frank Perrotta  &LR; at the
Boston Globe,  &UR; 617-929-2597. &LR;  For individual purchase of graphics
or photos please call 212 556-4204 or -1927.
</P>
<P>
   All stories will bear the BOS designator.
</P>
<P>
   &UR;  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; INTERNATIONAL (i) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-TALKS (Jerusalem) _ Israeli and Palestinian negotiators
lay out divergent positions on the core issues of their dispute as
they open the most difficult chapter in the peace process. By
Charles M. Sennott. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   MOSCOW-FEAR (Moscow) _ Security is tightened in Russian cities
after a second deadly blast in four days rocks Moscow, flattening
an apartment building, killing at least 49 people and trapping
possibly dozens more. By David Filipov and Brian Whitmore. 1000
words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON (w) &LR;
