<TEXT>
<P>
   The following Arizona Republic story has been added for use by
clients of the NYTimes News Service for Tuesday, Sept. 14. If you
have any questions, please contact the Republic News Desk at (602)
444-8286.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN (Undated) - Of course there's an on-going cover-up
involving the tragedy at Waco, but it has nothing to do with the
FBI or the ATF or pyrotechnic devices or mysterious rifle shell
casings or missing reports. The cause of death for the 80 men,
women and children in the Branch Dividian compound was America's
most efficient and predictable killer _ impatience. Not theirs.
Ours. By E.J. MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and ``K''
categories. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
