<P>
   CLINTON-TIMOR (Auckland, New Zealand) _ Hundreds of U.S. troops
could be on their way to East Timor within days if Indonesia allows
a rapid deployment of an Australian-led security force, White House
officials say. The United States and other nations gathered for the
Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation forum also intend to hold
Indonesian President B.J. Habibie to his word by continuing to
withhold military contracts and loan guarantees until the
peacekeepers are on the island. By NANCY MATHIS.
