<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-09-13 21:31 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A0855 &Cx1f; tdt-z
u s BC-GLF-RYDER-ESTES-BOS &LR;      09-13 0295
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GLF-RYDER-ESTES-BOS </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
ESTES ON TAP, IF NECESSARY 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By JIM MCCABE  
 c.1999 The Boston Globe  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   BROOKLINE, Mass. _ It was love at first sight, but whether Bob
Estes gets another date with The Country Club depends on another
love _ Davis Love.
</P>
<P>
   All indications are that Love will be healthy enough to play in
next week's Ryder Cup matches, but if he isn't, Estes _ as the 11th
player in the standings _ would get the call. And to prepare for
his role as pinch hitter, Estes got a tour of the course Monday. He
played a crisp three-hour round with Don Callahan, the director of
golf at TCC.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's my kind of course,'' said the 33-year-old Estes, who tied
for 15th at the Canadian Open Sunday. ``I like older, more
traditional-styled courses, where it's more about position than
brute strength.''
</P>
<P>
   Love, who has played on three Ryder Cup teams and provides
valuable experience for captain Ben Crenshaw, was diagnosed Aug. 29
with a pinched nerve in his back a day after the NEC Invitational.
He hasn't played since, as doctors advised him to rest.
</P>
<P>
   Vernon Spratley of Pros Inc., indicated last week that Love
would be ready for the Ryder Cup, and a call to that office Monday
confirmed that that is still the case.
</P>
<P>
   Estes understands the situation, and that there is no timetable.
If Love is ready, he said, that is best for everyone.
</P>
<P>
   ``After all, he's the fourth-ranked player in the world,'' said
Estes. ``We need him.''
</P>
<P>
   If not the Ryder Cup, Estes will head to the Texas Open in San
Antonio, which is a pleasant thought, since that's where he secured
his only PGA Tour win, in 1994.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not like I'm in a bad position,'' said Estes. ``I'm not
stressed out about it.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
