hyperspectral-camera data. The human eye sees three bands in the
visible spectrum, while Landsat, called a multispectral instrument,
records six bands of light. The hyperspectral instrument used in
Yellowstone records 128 bands, in information blocks, or pixels,
one meter square. (Jim Robbins/New York Times Photo) LITE
