<P>
   ATTENTION EDITORS: The following photos are part of tonight's
New York Times Photo Package, moving Monday, 09/13/99. Photo
clients will automatically receive these photos via AP's
PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases by calling
(888) 603-1036 or 212-556-4204.
</P>
<P>
   (NYT37) GETTYSBURG, Pa. -- Sept. 13, 1999 --
GETTYSBURG-CONFLICT-2, 09-13 -- ``Nowhere in the Park Service
mission do you find that I have a responsibility to protect the
commercial enterprises surrounding the park,'' says Dr. John A.
Latschar, park superintendant, of the nearby shops that some
visitors find tawdry and others colorful. Rather, he claims a
responsibility to visitors who annually flood 1.7-million strong
into the busiest of the Civil War parks. (John Zeedick/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT36) GETTYSBURG, Pa. -- Sept. 13, 1999 --
GETTYSBURG-CONFLICT-1, 09-13 -- A viewing platform atop the
Cyclorama in Gettysburg is often filled with people. This is a
major tourist attraction, built around a light show and Paul
Philippoteaux's 360-degree painting of Pickett's Charge, a vivid
moment in the three days of Gettysburg fighting. (John Zeedick/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT35) NEW YORK -- Sept. 13, 1999 -- PATTERNS-FASHION, 09-13 --
Amy Wesson, who came to prominence in advertising campaigns for
designers like Valentino, is returning to modeling after drug
rehabilitation. ``I really thought I had things in control,'' she
says. ``I was a mess, and everyone knew it.'' (Thomas Dallal/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT34) NEW YORK -- Sept. 13, 1999 -- NY-FASHION-2, 09-13 -- So
many celebrities, so many hot pants to sell. From left, Mark
Kroeker's variation on a deconstructed slip; Gregory Parkinson's
sheer skirt and jersey top; at Versus by Donatella Versace, a
grommeted leather mini and torn top. (Corina Lecca/New York Times
Photo) LITE
</P>
<P>
