<P>
   &UR; COMPLAIN _  &LR;  Hungry, angry and sleep-deprived, Sue Johnson
wandered through a deserted Houston airline terminal at 1 a.m.,
muttering like a mad woman. Continental Airlines had canceled her
connecting flight to San Antonio, failed to give her the proper
paperwork to secure her a spot on a competing carrier, then merely
shrugged when telling her she'd have to stay the night. ``It was a
nightmare trip,'' the graphic designer from San Antonio recalled.
``Unbelievably awful.'' Back home, too irate to write and too vexed
to vent on paper, Johnson instead booted up her computer and, for
$19.95, hired Complain.com to articulate her gripe for her. All it
took was one tart letter from the Internet consumer advocacy
company for Johnson to receive a $200 voucher from the airline. By
Sam McManis
