 &UR; PALM  &LR; _ Seeking to cash in on the popularity of the Palm Pilot,
3Com said yesterday it plans to spin off its Palm Computing
Division into a separate publicly traded company. By Deborah
Solomon
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; WINE &LR;  _ In the first major consolidation among online wine vendors,
VirtualVineyard.com of Palo Alto will announce today that it has
acquired Wine.com of Napa. In the wine industry, labels are often
worth more than what's inside the bottle. That also seems to be the
case in this merger, where wine.com is the catchier name and will
be the survivor. Although no purchase price will be disclosed,
sources close to the merger say it may top the $3.3 million price
that Compaq Computer reportedly paid last month to acquire the
altavista.com domain name for its search engine subsidiary. By
Peter Sinton
