<HEADLINE>
RIDEAUX COULD RETURN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ USC freshman cornerback Darrell Rideaux seems
likely to play Saturday against San Diego State, although his back
injury could limit his role in the secondary.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't think he'll be 100 percent, but he'll be available,''
USC coach Paul Hackett said. ``We'll have to see how the week goes.
Hopefully, the rest gave him some strength back and didn't pound
him down.''
</P>
<P>
   The more interesting question seems to be Rideaux's injury
itself. Rideaux said he had back spasms following USC's practice
Sunday night. But according to several sources, he actually has a
stress fracture suffered last June when a runner collided with him
at the state track championships.
</P>
<P>
   Rideaux said his back is ``a day-to-day thing'' but again
downplayed the possibility he would redshirt.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's not a factor. At this point, we don't think the injury is
that severe,'' Rideaux said. ``That decision will be made by coach
Hackett in the upcoming days.''
</P>
<P>
   Hackett was a little less certain to rule out the possibility of
redshirting.
</P>
<P>
   ``That would be a long shot. It's not out of the question but
unlikely,'' Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Rideaux missed USC's opener with Hawaii and the Trojans' depth
at cornerback is a problem with freshman Kevin Arbet expected to
miss this week's contest with a sprained ankle. That leaves senior
Tanqueray Clark and sophomore Eric Reese to compete for the nickel
back position, unless Rideaux is able to play.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a matter of where do I fit in the game plan,'' Rideaux
said. ``Now I have to find out where do I fit in.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Garner update: Junior wide receiver Troy Garner of Notre Dame
High will meet with Hackett this week regarding his two-week
suspension from the team. Garner was suspended during training camp
at UC Irvine after arguing with strength coach Matt Schiotz.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're going to get together this week to clear the air,''
Hackett said. ``I would anticipate he would be back if not this
coming week, then the following week.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Scouting report: After watching game tapes of San Diego
State's loss to Illinois, Hackett was encouraged by the way the
Illini's defense harassed Aztecs quarterbacks Brian Russell and
Jack Hawley into completing only 17 of 40 passes for 179 yards.
</P>
<P>
   ``The quarterbacks did not play particularly well,'' Hackett
said. ``Illinois did some things that could help us.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Oregon time announced: USC's game with Oregon on Sept. 25
will have a 7:15 p.m. kickoff and be televised on Fox Sports West.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans' game with Oregon State at the Coliseum on Oct. 2
will either kickoff at 12:30 p.m. or 3:30 p.m., with 3:30 the most
likely time.
</P>
<P>
   __ They're No. 1: Based on their 62 points against Hawaii, the
Trojans find themselves No. 1 in the country in the NCAA national
rankings for scoring offense.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans are also tied for first in turnover margin at
plus-3.
</P>
</TEXT>
